    "method": "chemical synthesis",
    "description": "Produced in two steps: (1) sorbitan (from sorbitol) is reacted with oleic acid to form sorbitan monooleate, then (2) ethoxylated with approximately 20 units of ethylene oxide. Oleic acid is typically sourced from vegetable oils."
